Musk strives for delivery record
Tesla’s quarter might break record. The electric car group experienced losses despite delivery boom.
New York. With the prospect of record numbers, Tesla head Elon Musk caused his electric car company's stock to boom. “We have the chance to reach our first quarter with 100,000 deliveries”, Musk wrote in an email for Tesla employees published by the business blog “Electrek”.
